      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Tally Last Week in Connecticut, New Jersey and New York.</p>
        <p>Senate</p>
        <p>1. Hate Crimes:  Vote on an amendment to a defense authorization bill that would expand federal jurisdiction for crimes based on race, religion and national origin, and would add sex and handicapped status to the categories covered, as well as sexual orientation. Approved 57 to 42, June 20.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Tally Last Week in Connecticut, New Jersey and New York.</p>
        <p>Senate</p>
        <p>1. Hate Crimes:  Vote on an amendment to a defense authorization bill that would expand federal jurisdiction for crimes based on race, religion and national origin, and would add sex and handicapped status to the categories covered, as well as sexual orientation. Approved 57 to 42, June 20.</p>
        <p>2. Cuban Embargo:  Vote to kill an amendment to a defense authorization bill that would create a commission to study the effectiveness of the American economic embargo against Cuba. Approved 59 to 41, June 20.</p>
        <p>3. Aid to Colombian Military:  Vote to kill an amendment to a foreign aid bill that would transfer $225 million in aid from the Colombian military to drug treatment and prevention programs in the United States.  Approved 89 to 11, June 21.</p>
        <p>4. Aid to Colombian Military:  Vote on an amendment to a foreign aid bill that would cut the aid package for the Colombian military to $200 million, from $934 million. Rejected 79 to 19, June 21.</p>
        <p>5. Workplace Injuries:  Vote on an amendment to a spending bill for the Departments of Labor and Health and Human Services that would delay by one year federal regulations requiring employers to take steps to prevent repetitive motion injuries. Rejected 57 to 41, June 22.</p>
        <p>6. Prescription Drugs:  Vote on a amendment to a spending bill for the Departments of Labor and Health and Human Services that would lower drug prices for Medicare beneficiaries. Rejected 53 to 44, June 22.</p>
