        <p>House</p>
        <p>1. Tobacco:  Vote on an amendment to a spending bill for the Department of Veterans Affairs that would block the department's plans to give the Justice Department $4 million to help pay for the federal lawsuit against the tobacco industry. Approved 207 to 197, June 19. The following day, the House reversed itself and by voice vote approved the transfer.</p>
        <p>2. Tobacco:  Vote on an amendment to a bill financing the Departments of Commerce, State and Justice that would let the Justice Department accept $12 million from other agencies to pay for the lawsuit against the tobacco industry. Approved 215 to 183, June 23.</p>
